This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to autonomous driving, which suggests that it would likely fall under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular tool in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of segmentation techniques to simplify and unify detection tasks, which could fall under the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses concerns related to computation time and detection performance, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
